cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.HC, cs.CV

The paper deals with modeling the time-varying subjective quality of video streams, which involves aspects of multimedia (cs.MM), networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of rate-adaptive HTTP video streaming technologies also suggests a focus on networking and multimedia. Therefore, cs.MM and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.IT, cs.HC, and cs.CV.
